# === IDE ===
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# === Obsidian vault state (per-machine UI; baseline config committed) ===
# Repo is opened as Obsidian vault for local navigation (DEC-DEV-0046, Stage 2).
# Commit: app.json, appearance.json, core-plugins.json, community-plugins.json,
# hotkeys.json — shared baseline across machines/versions.
# Ignore: per-session UI state + graph view position/zoom + cache.
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/graph.json
.obsidian/cache/
.obsidian/*.json.bak

# === OS ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# === Backups & swap ===
*.bak
*.backup
*.swp
*~

# === Local secrets (NEVER commit) ===
.env
.env.local
secrets/

# === Logs ===
*.log

# === Node (if tooling added) ===
node_modules/
package-lock.json

# === Drafts & intermediate (keep main clean) ===
_drafts/
_design-history/
WORK-IN-PROGRESS.md
*.draft.md

# === Test artifacts ===
.test-output/
fixtures/local/

# === Work-rails generated index (regenerable projection — run rails-build.js) ===
# Outputs are derived from git log; committing them across many branches/worktrees
# = merge churn. Tracked: rail-areas.json + README.md. Regenerate on demand.
dev/meta-improvement/rails/RAILS.md
dev/meta-improvement/rails/rails-rollup.ndjson

# === Claude Code state (anywhere inside ecosystem repo) ===
# Ecosystem repo itself does NOT use .claude/ — its content lives in
# commands/, skills/, etc. at root (they get COPIED to user's .claude/
# during bootstrap). If Claude Code creates .claude/ anywhere inside
# this repo (subagents with isolation=worktree, local experiments, etc.),
# don't track it.
#
# Exception (Phase 4.1, DEC-DEV-0034): track ecosystem-repo-local slash
# commands under .claude/commands/ so /meta:* surfaces when working in
# the ecosystem repo itself. settings.local.json, worktrees/, and other
# private state stay ignored.
**/.claude/
!/.claude/
/.claude/*
!/.claude/commands/
!/.claude/commands/**

# Форматированные бинарные артефакты владельца не трекаем (дубль REPORT.md; DEC-DEV deadweight-sweep)
dev/universality-assessment/*.pdf
